<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880531-0029 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Concord Fabrics Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CIS </CO><IN> BBK </IN><TEXT>   Concord Fabrics Inc., New York, merged into a subsidiary, effecting an anti-takeover measure.    With the transaction, each of the fabric maker's shares outstanding has been converted into one Class A share plus one Class B share. The Class A shares each carry one vote, and the Class B shares each have 10 votes; the Class A stock has a higher dividend rate, however.    The Weinstein family holds about 62% of Concord. The company's name won't change, but Concord now is incorporated in Delaware rather than in New York.    At the start of trading today, the Class A shares will be listed on the American Stock Exchange under the symbol CIS, which is the current symbol. The Class B shares will trade under the symbol CISB. </TEXT></DOC>